{"title_page": "Rob Pike", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = THILINA CHAMITH DILHAN AMARASINGHE\n| image       = Rob-pike-oscon.jpg\n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth year and age|1997}} <!-- {{Birth date and age|1956|MM|DD}} -->\n| birth_place =  AVISSAWELLA\n| death_date  = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place = \n| nationality = SRI LANKAN\n| other_names = ASHI WEB DEVELOPER\n| employer    = [[FOUNDER @ ASHI WEB DESIGN]]\n| occupation  = [[Software engineer]]\n| website     = {{URL|https://ashiwebdesign.com/}}\n}}'''\n                                                    THILINA CHAMITH DILHAN''''''Bold text'''\n                                                    \nI'm 22 years old, a regular guy who comes from a small country in Asia (Sri Lanka). I love little things in life and never take myself too seriously. Laughing with friends and enjoying life with my family are two of my favourite things.\n\nBut, that wasn't always true.\n\nSince very young age I have been passionate about computers, like any other kid, right? Surely, but with one difference. I wanted to know how do things work in the background, how all those programs are made etc., and I wanted to become a programmer.\n\nI was sitting all day at my computer and trying to find some online books to read/learn more about coding because at the time YouTube wasn't like now and we didn't have a strong internet connection to be able to watch related videos, so the books were all we had.\n\nAs soon as I started looking for books, I've realized that if I want to learn more about coding, I have to learn the English language first, because all those great books are written in English.\n\nAt the time, I was still in the primary school, so I had only one option; to learn English and start learning about coding on my own.\n\nSince the political/financial situation is awful here, I knew that I would never be able to reach the lifestyle I wanted if I chose the second option, so my choice was above option.\n\nSince I'm passionate about web developing (by profession software engineer), I've made a decision and started this website.\n\n'''My Interests'''\n                                                                       \n  MUSIC\n  TRAVELLING\n  CODING\n  READING\n  ERROR FINDER\n  PLAY GAME\n  \n  '''CONTACT INFO\n''''''Bold text'''\n\nEmail : Thilinachamith1997@gmail.com\n\nPhone Number : +94 717551511\n\nFacebook : https://www.facebook.com/ashiwebdeveloper\n\nLinkdin : https://lk.linkedin.com/in/thilina-chamith-829003184\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Rob C. Pike\n| image       = Rob-pike-oscon.jpg\n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth year and age|1956}} <!-- {{Birth date and age|1956|MM|DD}} -->\n| birth_place = \n| death_date  = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place = \n| nationality = Canadian\n| other_names = \n| known_for   = [[Plan 9 from Bell Labs|Plan 9]], [[UTF-8]], [[Golang|Go]]\n| employer    = [[Google]]\n| occupation  = [[Software engineer]]\n| spouse      = [[Ren\u00e9e French]]\n| alma_mater         = {{plainlist|\n*[[University of Toronto]] {{small|([[Bachelor of Science|BS]])}}\n*[[California Institute of Technology]]}}\n| website     = {{URL|http://herpolhode.com/rob/}}\n}}\n'''Robert''' \"'''Rob'''\" '''C. Pike''' (born 1956) is a Canadian [[programmer]] and [[author]]. He is best known for his work on the [[Go (programming language)|Go programming language]] and at [[Bell Labs]], where he was a member of the [[Unix]] team and was involved in the creation of the [[Plan 9 from Bell Labs]] and [[Inferno (operating system)|Inferno]] operating systems, as well as the [[Limbo programming language]].\n\nHe also co-developed the [[Blit (computer terminal)|Blit]] graphical terminal for Unix; before that he wrote the first window system for Unix in 1981. Pike is the sole inventor named in AT&T's US patent 4,555,775 or \"[[backing store]] [[patent]]\" that is part of the X graphic system protocol and one of the first software patents.<ref>{{cite web|author=Rob |url=http://commandcenter.blogspot.com/2006/06/i-cant-find-this-on-web-so-here.html |title=Command Center |publisher=Commandcenter.blogspot.com |date=2006-06-11 |accessdate=2013-06-25}}</ref>\n\nOver the years Pike has written many text editors; [[Sam (text editor)|sam]]<ref name=\"reader\">{{cite techreport |first1=M. D. |last1=McIlroy |authorlink1=Doug McIlroy |year=1987 |url=http://www.cs.dartmouth.edu/~doug/reader.pdf |title=A Research Unix reader: annotated excerpts from the Programmer's Manual, 1971\u20131986 |series=CSTR |number=139 |institution=Bell Labs}}</ref> and [[Acme (text editor)|acme]] are the most well known and are still in active use and development.\n\nPike, with [[Brian Kernighan]], is the co-author of ''[[The Practice of Programming]]'' and ''[[The Unix Programming Environment (book)|The Unix Programming Environment]]''. With [[Ken Thompson (computer programmer)|Ken Thompson]] he is the co-creator of [[UTF-8]]. Pike also developed lesser systems such as the [[vismon]] program for displaying faces of email authors.\n\nPike also appeared once on ''[[Late Night with David Letterman]]'', as a technical assistant to the comedy duo [[Penn & Teller]].\n\nPike works for [[Google]], where he is involved in the creation of the programming languages  [[Go (programming language)|Go]] and [[Sawzall (programming language)|Sawzall]].<ref>\n{{cite journal\n|first1=Rob\n|last1=Pike\n|first2=Sean\n|last2=Dorward\n|first3=Robert\n|last3=Griesemer\n|first4=Sean\n|last4=Quinlan\n|journal=Scientific Programming\n|volume=13\n|issue=4\n|pages=227\u2013298\n|date=2005-01-01\n|url=http://research.google.com/archive/sawzall.html\n|title=Interpreting the Data: Parallel Analysis with Sawzall\n}}</ref>\n\nPike is married to author and illustrator [[Ren\u00e9e French]]; the couple live in both the US and Australia.<ref name=\"wowxwow\">\n{{cite web\n|url=https://wowxwow.com/artist-interview/renee-french-ai\n|website=WOW x WOW \n|title=Renee French \u2013 A River Runs Through It \u2013 Artist Interview\n|date=27 July 2015\n}}\n</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*The [[Plumber (program)|plumber]] \u2013 the interprocess communications mechanism used in Plan 9 and Inferno\n*[[Mark V. Shaney]] \u2013 an artificial Usenet poster designed by Pike\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* [http://herpolhode.com/rob/ugly.pdf The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly: The Unix Legacy] \u2013 Slides of his presentation at the commemoration of 1000000000 seconds of the Unix clock.[http://doc.cat-v.org/bell_labs/good_bad_ugly/slides.pdf Archive on cat-v.org]\n* [http://doc.cat-v.org/bell_labs/utah2000/ Systems Software Research is Irrelevant] (a.k.a. utah2000) [http://herpolhode.com/rob/utah2000.pdf slides][http://herpolhode.com/rob/utah2000.ps ps file]\n* [http://herpolhode.com/rob/ Pike's personal homepage]\n* [http://research.google.com/people/r/ Pike's Google homepage]\n* [http://genius.cat-v.org/rob-pike/ Pike's page on cat-v.org]\n* [http://www.quut.com/c/rob/index.html Pike's page on C archive]\n* [https://interviews.slashdot.org/story/04/10/18/1153211/rob-pike-responds Questions and Answers with Rob Pike] by Robin \"Roblimo\" Miller (published in Slashdot in October 2004)\n* [http://www.informit.com/articles/article.aspx?p=1623555 Interview on informit.com][http://www.informit.com/articles/article.aspx?p=1941206 Another interview]\n* [https://www.infoworld.com/article/2625481/google-executive-frustrated-by-java--c---complexity.html Interview on infoworld.com]\n* [https://www.red-gate.com/simple-talk/opinion/geek-of-the-week/rob-pike-geek-of-the-week/ Interview on red-gate.com]\n* [https://usesthis.com/interviews/rob.pike/ Interview on usesthis.com]\n* {{YouTube|hB05UFqOtFA|Concurrency/message passing Newsqueak}} (Google Tech Talks May 9, 2007)\n* [http://doc.cat-v.org/bell_labs/structural_regexps/ Structural Regular Expressions by Rob Pike] [http://doc.cat-v.org/bell_labs/structural_regexps/se.pdf slides]\n* [http://doc.cat-v.org/bell_labs/utf-8_history The history of UTF-8 as told by Rob Pike][https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~mgk25/ucs/utf-8-history.txt text file]\n* {{YouTube|z4iVAcYyWN0|Pike's appearance with Penn & Teller on Letterman}}\n\n{{Rob Pike navbox}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pike, Rob}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Canadian computer scientists]]\n[[Category:Computer programmers]]\n[[Category:Canadian technology writers]]\n[[Category:Unix people]]\n[[Category:Google employees]]\n[[Category:Plan 9 people]]\n[[Category:Inferno (operating system) people]]\n[[Category:Scientists at Bell Labs]]\n[[Category:Programming language designers]]\n", "name_user": "Chamith dilhan", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rob_Pike"}
{"title_page": "Lucien Maelfait", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Lucien Maelfait\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1919|7|30|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Havr\u00e9]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = \n}}\n'''Lucien Maelfait''' (born 30 July 1919) was a French [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. He rode in the [[1949 Tour de France]].<ref name=\"mdc1949\">{{cite web|url=http://memoire-du-cyclisme.net/eta_tdf_1947_1977/tdf1949.php|publisher=Memoire du cyclisme|title=36\u00e8me Tour de France 1949|language=French|accessdate=8 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120124102917/http://www.memoire-du-cyclisme.net/eta_tdf_1947_1977/tdf1949.php|archivedate=24 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|14387}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maelfait, Lucien}}\n[[Category:1919 births]]\n[[Category:Possibly living people]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Hainaut (province)]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n{{France-cycling-bio-1910s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Lucien Maelfait\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1919|7|30|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Havr\u00e9]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwi